Interface Invalidate<K>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - key type (identifies entries to remove)
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AbstractCache<K,V>, AbstractUncheckedVolatileCache<K,V>, AbstractVolatileCache<K,V>, Cache<K,V>, CacheRemover<K,V,D>, LoaderCache<K,V>, LoaderRemoverCache<K,V,D>, RemoverCache<K,V,D>, UncheckedCache<K,V>, UncheckedLoaderCache<K,V>, UncheckedVolatileCache<K,V>, UncheckedVolatileLoaderCache<K,V>, VolatileCache<K,V>, VolatileLoaderCache<K,V>, VolatileLoaderRemoverCache<K,V,D>, VolatileRemoverCache<K,V,D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCacheKeyAdapter, BoundedSoftRefLoaderCache, CacheAsUncheckedCacheAdapter, CacheKeyAdapter, DirtyDiskCellCache, DiskCellCache, GuardedStrongRefLoaderCache, GuardedStrongRefLoaderRemoverCache, IoSync, LoaderCacheAsCacheAdapter, LoaderCacheKeyAdapter, LoaderRemoverCacheAsLoaderCacheAdapter, LoaderRemoverCacheAsRemoverCacheAdapter, LoaderRemoverCacheKeyAdapter, RemoverCacheAsCacheAdapter, RemoverCacheKeyAdapter, SoftRefLoaderCache, SoftRefLoaderRemoverCache, VolatileCacheAsUncheckedVolatileCacheAdapter, VolatileLoaderCacheAsVolatileCacheAdapter, WeakRefLoaderCache, WeakRefVolatileCache, WeakRefVolatileLoaderCache

    public interface Invalidate<K>
    A collection of methods that invalidate cache entries. It is possible to invalidate everything, entries matching some condition, or an individual entry.

    "Invalidate" means: Remove from the cache, and discard any changes that have been made in this cache or any backing cache. In particular, if changes have been persisted to disk, remove those as well.

    This interface is extended both by the caches and by CacheRemover. See AbstractCache and CacheRemover, for more specific documentation for each case.

    Author:
    Tobias Pietzsch
